t into pieces (approx. 2 cm)","100 g breadcrumbs of choice (see Tips)","5 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","1 tsp ground coriander","½ tsp ground cayenne pepper","½ tsp ground cinnamon","½ tsp ground cumin","2 lemons, 1 zested, no white pith and 1 cut into halves lengthways, then into thin slices","¼ tsp salt, plus extra to taste","1 - 2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra to taste","250 g broccoli, cut into florets, including approx. 2 cm of stalk"]},{"title":"Turmeric tahini dressing","content":["20 g pine nuts","60 g tahini (see Tips)","120 g filtered water","1 tbsp lemon juice","¼ tsp salt","2 garlic cloves","½ tsp ground turmeric"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["60 g rocket","½ red onion, cut into thin slices","1 carrot, cut into julienne","1 Lebanese cucumber, cut into cubes (1-2 cm)","4 pita breads"]}],"id":"r341247","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-gCawxgAoLoQ\/XZVQ4Q2rSPI\/AAAAAAAAdG4\/apBtPOvzJcY23lapOwu-izTENcmXN38BgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0__CLFCWVwdrw4uBvM.png","title":"Eggplant and porcini bites with turmeric tahini dressing","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19.5 g","fat":"21.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"58.7 g","calories":"2272 kJ \/ 541 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, sealable container, serving bowls, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own breadcrumbs, place 200 g bread into mixing bowl and chop <strong>9-10 sec\/speed 4.<\/strong>","To make your own tahini, refer to the recipe on Cookidoo (www.cookidoo.com.au).","To make this recipe gluten free, use gluten free breadcrumbs and serve with gluten free pita bread (or flatbread).","Make sure you discard the last tablespoon of the porcini mushroom soaking liquid as this may contain any sediment from soaking.","You can store leftover Turmeric tahini dressing in a sealable container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","55m","4 portions"]}